#: l10n/source/edge.xml:157
msgid "Adding BareMetalHost inventory"
msgstr "Adición del inventario de BareMetalHost"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:158
msgid ""
"Registering bare-metal servers for automated deployment requires creating "
"two resources: a Secret storing BMC access credentials and a "
"Metal<superscript>3</superscript> BareMetalHost resource defining the BMC "
"connection and other details:"
msgstr ""
"El registro de servidores bare metal para el despliegue automatizado "
"requiere la creación de dos recursos: un secreto que almacena las "
"credenciales de acceso a BMC y un recurso BareMetalHost de "
"Metal<superscript>3</superscript> que define la conexión de BMC y otros "
"detalles:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:159
msgid "Note the following:"
msgstr "Tenga en cuenta lo siguiente:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:160
msgid ""
"The Secret username/password must be base64 encoded. Note this should not "
"include any trailing newlines (for example, use <literal>echo -n</literal>, "
"not just <literal>echo</literal>!)"
msgstr ""
"El nombre de usuario y la contraseña del secreto deben estar cifrados en "
"base64. No deben incluir saltos de línea al final (por ejemplo, use "
"<literal>echo -n</literal>, no solo <literal>echo</literal>)"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:161
msgid ""
"The <literal>cluster-role</literal> label may be set now or later on cluster "
"creation. In the example below, we expect <literal>control-plane</literal> "
"or <literal>worker</literal>"
msgstr ""
"La etiqueta <literal>cluster-role</literal> se puede establecer ahora o más "
"adelante, durante la creación del clúster. En el ejemplo siguiente, se "
"espera <literal>control-plane</literal> o <literal>worker</literal>"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:162
msgid ""
"<literal>bootMACAddress</literal> must be a valid MAC that matches the "
"control plane NIC of the host"
msgstr ""
"<literal>bootMACAddress</literal> debe ser una dirección MAC válida que "
"coincida con la NIC de plano de control del host"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:163
msgid ""
"The <literal>bmc</literal> address is the connection to the BMC management "
"API, the following are supported:"
msgstr ""
"La dirección <literal>bmc</literal> es la conexión a la API de gestión de "
"BMC. Se admiten las siguientes:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:164
msgid ""
"<literal>redfish-virtualmedia://&lt;IP ADDRESS&gt;/redfish/v1/Systems/"
"&lt;SYSTEM ID&gt;</literal>: Redfish virtual media, for example, SuperMicro"
msgstr ""
"<literal>redfish-virtualmedia://&lt;DIRECCIÓN IP&gt;/redfish/v1/Systems/"
"&lt;ID DEL SISTEMA&gt;</literal>: medio virtual Redfish, por ejemplo, "
"SuperMicro"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:165
msgid ""
"<literal>idrac-virtualmedia://&lt;IP ADDRESS&gt;/redfish/v1/Systems/"
"System.Embedded.1</literal>: Dell iDRAC"
msgstr ""
"<literal>idrac-virtualmedia://&lt;DIRECCIÓN IP&gt;/redfish/v1/Systems/"
"System.Embedded.1</literal>: iDRAC de Dell"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:166
msgid ""
"See the <link xl:href=\"https://github.com/metal3-io/baremetal-operator/blob/"
"main/docs/api.md\">Upstream API docs</link> for more details on the "
"BareMetalHost API"
msgstr ""
"Consulte la <link xl:href=\"https://github.com/metal3-io/baremetal-operator/"
"blob/main/docs/api.md\">documentación original de la API</link> para obtener "
"más información sobre la API de BareMetalHost"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:167
msgid "Configuring Static IPs"
msgstr "Configuración de IP estáticas"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:168
msgid ""
"The BareMetalHost example above assumes DHCP provides the controlplane "
"network configuration, but for scenarios where manual configuration is "
"needed such as static IPs it is possible to provide additional "
"configuration, as described below."
msgstr ""
"El ejemplo anterior de BareMetalHost presupone que DHCP proporciona la "
"configuración de red del plano de control, pero para situaciones en las que "
"se necesite una configuración manual, como en el caso de las IP estáticas, "
"es posible proporcionar una configuración adicional, como se describe a "
"continuación."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:169
msgid "Additional script for static network configuration"
msgstr "Guion adicional para la configuración de la red estática"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:170
msgid ""
"When creating the base image with Edge Image Builder, in the "
"<literal>network</literal> folder, create the following <literal>configure-"
"network.sh</literal> file."
msgstr ""
"Al crear la imagen base con Edge Image Builder, en la carpeta de "
"<literal>network</literal>, cree el archivo <literal>configure-network.sh</"
"literal> siguiente."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:171
msgid ""
"This consumes configuration drive data on first-boot, and configures the "
"host networking using the <link xl:href=\"https://github.com/suse-edge/nm-"
"configurator\">NM Configurator tool</link>."
msgstr ""
"Esto consume datos de la unidad de configuración en el primer arranque y "
"configura la red del host usando la <link xl:href=\"https://github.com/suse-"
"edge/nm-configurator\">herramienta NM Configurator</link>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:172
msgid "Additional secret with host network configuration"
msgstr "Secreto adicional con configuración de red de host"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:173
msgid ""
"An additional secret containing data in the <link xl:href=\"https://"
"nmstate.io/\">nmstate</link> format supported by NM Configurator (<xref "
"linkend=\"components-nmc\"/>) can be defined for each host."
msgstr ""
"Se puede definir un secreto adicional que contenga datos en el formato <link "
"xl:href=\"https://nmstate.io/\">nmstate</link> compatible con NM "
"Configurator (<xref linkend=\"components-nmc\"/>) para cada host."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:174
msgid ""
"The secret is then referenced in the <literal>BareMetalHost</literal> "
"resource via the <literal>preprovisioningNetworkDataName</literal> spec "
"field."
msgstr ""
"A continuación, se hace referencia al secreto en el recurso "
"<literal>BareMetalHost</literal> mediante el campo de especificación "
"<literal>preprovisioningNetworkDataName</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:175
msgid ""
"In some circumstances the MAC address may be omitted. See <xref "
"linkend=\"networking-unified\"/> for additional details."
msgstr ""
"En algunas circunstancias, la dirección MAC puede omitirse. Consulte la "
"<xref linkend=\"networking-unified\"/> para obtener más detalles."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:176
msgid "BareMetalHost preparation"
msgstr "Preparación de BareMetalHost"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:177
msgid ""
"After creating the BareMetalHost resource and associated secrets as "
"described above, a host preparation workflow is triggered:"
msgstr ""
"Después de crear el recurso BareMetalHost y los secretos asociados como se "
"ha descrito, se activa un flujo de trabajo de preparación del host:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:178
msgid ""
"A ramdisk image is booted by virtualmedia attachment to the target host BMC"
msgstr ""
"Se arranca una imagen ramdisk mediante la conexión de un dispositivo virtual "
"al BMC del host de destino"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:179
msgid ""
"The ramdisk inspects hardware details, and prepares the host for "
"provisioning (for example by cleaning disks of previous data)"
msgstr ""
"El ramdisk inspecciona los detalles del hardware y prepara el host para el "
"aprovisionamiento (por ejemplo, limpiando los discos de datos anteriores)"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:180
msgid ""
"On completion of this process, hardware details in the BareMetalHost "
"<literal>status.hardware</literal> field are updated and can be verified"
msgstr ""
"Una vez completado este proceso, se actualizan los detalles del hardware en "
"el campo <literal>status.hardware</literal> de BareMetalHost y se pueden "
"verificar"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:181
msgid ""
"This process can take several minutes, but when completed you should see the "
"BareMetalHost state become <literal>available</literal>:"
msgstr ""
"Este proceso puede tardar varios minutos, pero una vez completado, debería "
"ver que el estado de BareMetalHost pasa a ser <literal>available</literal> "
"(disponible):"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:182
msgid "Creating downstream clusters"
msgstr "Creación de clústeres descendentes"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:183
msgid ""
"We now create Cluster API resources which define the downstream cluster, and "
"Machine resources which will cause the BareMetalHost resources to be "
"provisioned, then bootstrapped to form an RKE2 cluster."
msgstr ""
"Ahora creamos recursos de Cluster API que definen el clúster descendente y "
"recursos del equipo que provocarán que se aprovisionen los recursos de "
"BareMetalHost y, a continuación, se arranquen para formar un clúster RKE2."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:184
msgid "Control plane deployment"
msgstr "Despliegue del plano de control"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:185
msgid ""
"To deploy the controlplane we define a yaml manifest similar to the one "
"below, which contains the following resources:"
msgstr ""
"Para desplegar el plano de control, se define un manifiesto YAML similar al "
"que se muestra a continuación, que contiene los siguientes recursos:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:186
msgid ""
"Cluster resource defines the cluster name, networks, and type of "
"controlplane/infrastructure provider (in this case RKE2/Metal3)"
msgstr ""
"El recurso Cluster define el nombre del clúster, las redes y el tipo de "
"proveedor de plano de control/infraestructura (en este caso, RKE2/Metal3)"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:187
msgid ""
"Metal3Cluster defines the controlplane endpoint (host IP for single-node, "
"LoadBalancer endpoint for multi-node, this example assumes single-node)"
msgstr ""
"Metal3Cluster define el punto final del plano de control (IP del host para "
"un solo nodo, punto final LoadBalancer para varios nodos; en este ejemplo se "
"supone que hay un solo nodo)"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:188
msgid ""
"RKE2ControlPlane defines the RKE2 version and any additional configuration "
"needed during cluster bootstrapping"
msgstr ""
"RKE2ControlPlane define la versión de RKE2 y cualquier configuración "
"adicional necesaria durante el arranque del clúster"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:189
msgid ""
"Metal3MachineTemplate defines the OS Image to be applied to the "
"BareMetalHost resources, and the hostSelector defines which BareMetalHosts "
"to consume"
msgstr ""
"Metal3MachineTemplate define la imagen del sistema operativo que se aplicará "
"a los recursos BareMetalHost, y hostSelector define qué recursos "
"BareMetalHost se consumirán"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:190
msgid ""
"Metal3DataTemplate defines additional metaData to be passed to the "
"BareMetalHost (note networkData is not currently supported in the Edge "
"solution)"
msgstr ""
"Metal3DataTemplate define los metadatos adicionales que se pasarán a "
"BareMetalHost (tenga en cuenta que networkData no es compatible actualmente "
"con Edge)"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:191
msgid ""
"For simplicity this example assumes a single-node control plane where the "
"BareMetalHost is configured with an IP of <literal>192.168.125.200</"
"literal>. For more advanced multi-node examples, please see <xref "
"linkend=\"atip-automated-provisioning\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Para simplificar, en este ejemplo se entiende que hay un plano de control de "
"un solo nodo en el que BareMetalHost se ha configurado con la IP "
"<literal>192.168.125.200</literal>. Para ejemplos más avanzados de varios "
"nodos, consulte el <xref linkend=\"atip-automated-provisioning\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:192
msgid ""
"Once adapted to your environment, you can apply the example via "
"<literal>kubectl</literal> and then monitor the cluster status via "
"<literal>clusterctl</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Una vez adaptado a su entorno, puede aplicar el ejemplo mediante "
"<literal>kubectl</literal> y, a continuación, supervisar el estado del "
"clúster mediante <literal>clusterctl</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:193
msgid "Worker/Compute deployment"
msgstr "Despliegue de trabajadores/computación"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:194
msgid ""
"Similar to the control plane deployment, we define a YAML manifest which "
"contains the following resources:"
msgstr ""
"De forma similar al despliegue del plano de control, se define un manifiesto "
"YAML que contiene los siguientes recursos:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:195
msgid ""
"MachineDeployment defines the number of replicas (hosts) and the bootstrap/"
"infrastructure provider (in this case RKE2/Metal3)"
msgstr ""
"MachineDeployment define el número de réplicas (hosts) y el proveedor de "
"arranque/infraestructura (en este caso, RKE2/Metal3)"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:196
msgid ""
"RKE2ConfigTemplate describes the RKE2 version and first-boot configuration "
"for agent host bootstrapping"
msgstr ""
"RKE2ConfigTemplate describe la versión de RKE2 y la configuración de "
"arranque inicial para el arranque del host del agente"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:197
msgid ""
"Metal3MachineTemplate defines the OS Image to be applied to the "
"BareMetalHost resources, and the host selector defines which BareMetalHosts "
"to consume"
msgstr ""
"Metal3MachineTemplate define la imagen del sistema operativo que se aplicará "
"a los recursos BareMetalHost, y el selector de host define qué recursos "
"BareMetalHost se consumirán"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:198
msgid ""
"Metal3DataTemplate defines additional metadata to be passed to the "
"BareMetalHost (note that <literal>networkData</literal> is not currently "
"supported)"
msgstr ""
"Metal3DataTemplate define los metadatos adicionales que se pasarán a "
"BareMetalHost (tenga en cuenta que <literal>networkData</literal> no es "
"compatible actualmente)"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:199
msgid ""
"When the example above has been copied and adapted to suit your environment, "
"it can be applied via <literal>kubectl</literal> then the cluster status can "
"be monitored with <literal>clusterctl</literal>"
msgstr ""
"Una vez copiado y adaptado el ejemplo anterior a su entorno, se puede "
"aplicar mediante <literal>kubectl</literal> y, a continuación, se puede "
"supervisar el estado del clúster con <literal>clusterctl</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:200
msgid "Cluster deprovisioning"
msgstr "Desaprovisionamiento del clúster"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
