"xl:href=\"https://github.com/suse-edge/edge-image-builder/blob/release-1.3/"
"docs/debugging.md\">guía original sobre depuración</link>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:428
msgid "Testing your newly built image"
msgstr "Prueba de la imagen recién creada"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:429
msgid ""
"For instructions on how to test the newly built CRB image, refer to the "
"<link xl:href=\"https://github.com/suse-edge/edge-image-builder/blob/"
"release-1.3/docs/testing-guide.md\">upstream image testing guide</link>."
msgstr ""
"Para obtener instrucciones sobre cómo probar la imagen lista para arrancar "
"recién creada, consulte la <link xl:href=\"https://github.com/suse-edge/edge-"
"image-builder/blob/release-1.3/docs/testing-guide.md\">guía original sobre "
"pruebas de imágenes</link>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:431
msgid ""
"SUSE Multi-Linux Manager is included in SUSE Edge to provide automation and "
"control for keeping SUSE Linux Micro as the underlying operating system "
"consistently up-to-date on all nodes of your edge deployment. It can also be "
"used to manage Kubernetes and applications deployed on Kubernetes on your "
"edge nodes."
msgstr ""
"SUSE Multi-Linux Manager está incluido en SUSE Edge y proporciona "
"automatización y control con el fin de mantener el sistema operativo "
"subyacente SUSE Linux Micro constantemente actualizado en todos los nodos de "
"su despliegue periférico. También se puede usar para gestionar Kubernetes y "
"las aplicaciones desplegadas en Kubernetes en los nodos periféricos."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:432
msgid ""
"This quickstart guide is intended to get you up to speed with SUSE Multi-"
"Linux Manager as quickly as possible, with the goal of providing operating "
"system updates to your edge nodes. The quickstart guide doesn’t discuss "
"topics like sizing your storage, creating and managing additional software "
"channels for staging purposes, or managing users, system groups, and "
"organizations for larger deployments. For production use, we strongly "
"recommend to get familiar with the comprehensive <link xl:href=\"https://"
"documentation.suse.com/suma/5.0/en/suse-manager/index.html\">SUSE Multi-"
"Linux Manager Documentation</link>."
msgstr ""
"Esta guía de inicio rápido tiene como objetivo familiarizarle con SUSE Multi-"
"Linux Manager lo antes posible, con el fin de proporcionar actualizaciones "
"del sistema operativo a sus nodos periféricos. No aborda temas como el "
"dimensionamiento del almacenamiento, la creación y gestión de canales de "
"software adicionales con fines de preparación, ni la gestión de usuarios, "
"grupos de sistemas y organizaciones para despliegues de mayor envergadura. "
"Para su uso en producción, le recomendamos encarecidamente que se "
"familiarice con la completa <link xl:href=\"https://documentation.suse.com/"
"suma/5.0/en/suse-manager/index.html\">documentación de SUSE Multi-Linux "
"Manager</link>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:433
msgid ""
"The following steps are required to prepare SUSE Edge for using SUSE Multi-"
"Linux Manager effectively:"
msgstr ""
"Para preparar SUSE Edge a fin de que SUSE Multi-Linux Manager se use de "
"forma eficaz, es necesario seguir los siguientes pasos:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:434
msgid "Deploy and configure SUSE Multi-Linux Manager Server."
msgstr "Desplegar y configurar SUSE Multi-Linux Manager Server"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:435
msgid "Sync the SUSE Linux Micro package repositories."
msgstr "Sincronizar los repositorios de paquetes de SUSE Linux Micro"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:436
msgid "Create system groups."
msgstr "Crear grupos de sistemas"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:437
msgid "Create activation keys."
msgstr "Crear claves de activación"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:438
msgid ""
"Use Edge Image Builder to prepare installation media for SUSE Multi-Linux "
"Manager registration"
msgstr ""
"Usar Edge Image Builder para preparar el medio de instalación para el "
"registro de SUSE Multi-Linux Manager"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:439
msgid "Deploy SUSE Multi-Linux Manager Server"
msgstr "Despliegue de SUSE Multi-Linux Manager Server"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:440
msgid ""
"If you already have an instance of SUSE Multi-Linux Manager 5.0.5 running, "
"you can skip this step."
msgstr ""
"Si ya tiene una instancia de SUSE Multi-Linux Manager 5.0.5 en ejecución, "
"puede omitir este paso."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:441
msgid ""
"You can run SUSE Multi-Linux Manager Server on a dedicated physical server, "
"as a virtual machine on your own hardware, or in the cloud. Pre-configured "
"virtual machine images for SUSE Multi-Linux Server are provided for "
"supported public clouds."
msgstr ""
"Puede ejecutar SUSE Multi-Linux Manager Server en un servidor físico "
"dedicado, como máquina virtual en su propio hardware, o en la nube. Se "
"proporcionan imágenes de máquinas virtuales preconfiguradas para SUSE Multi-"
"Linux Server para las nubes públicas compatibles."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:442
msgid ""
"In this quick start we’re using the \"qcow2\" image <literal>SUSE-Manager-"
"Server.x86_64-5.0.4-Qcow-5.0-2025-04.qcow2</literal> for AMD64/Intel 64 that "
"you can find at <link xl:href=\"https://www.suse.com/download/suse-manager/"
"\">https://www.suse.com/download/suse-manager/</link> or in the SUSE "
"Customer Center. This image will work as a virtual machine on hypervisors "
"like KVM. Please always check for the newest version of the image and use it "
"for new installations."
msgstr ""
"En esta guía de inicio rápido se utiliza la imagen \"qcow2\" <literal>SUSE-"
"Manager-Server.x86_64-5.0.4-Qcow-5.0-2025-04.qcow2</literal> para AMD64/"
"Intel 64. La puede encontrar en <link xl:href=\"https://www.suse.com/"
"download/suse-manager/\">https://www.suse.com/download/suse-manager/</link> "
"o en el Centro de servicios al cliente de SUSE. Esta imagen funciona como "
"una máquina virtual en hipervisores como KVM. Compruebe siempre que dispone "
"de la versión más reciente de la imagen y utilícela para las nuevas "
"instalaciones."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:443
msgid ""
"You can also install SUSE Multi-Linux Manager Server on any of the other "
"supported hardware architectures. In that case pick the image that matches "
"your hardware architecture."
msgstr ""
"También puede instalar SUSE Multi-Linux Manager Server en cualquier otra "
"arquitectura de hardware compatible. En tal caso, elija la imagen que "
"coincida con su arquitectura de hardware."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:444
msgid ""
"Once you have downloaded the image, create a virtual machine that meets at "
"least the following minimal hardware specifications:"
msgstr ""
"Una vez que haya descargado la imagen, cree una máquina virtual que cumpla, "
"como mínimo, con las siguientes especificaciones de hardware:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:445
msgid "16 GB RAM"
msgstr "16 GB de RAM"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:446
msgid "4 physical or virtual cores"
msgstr "4 núcleos físicos o virtuales"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:447
msgid "an additional block device that has at least 100 GB"
msgstr "Un dispositivo de bloque adicional con una capacidad mínima de 100 GB"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:448
msgid ""
"With the qcow2 image, there is no need to install the operating system. You "
"can directly attach the image as your root partition."
msgstr ""
"Con la imagen qcow2, no es necesario instalar el sistema operativo. Puede "
"conectar directamente la imagen como su partición raíz."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:449
msgid ""
"You need to set up the network so that your edge nodes can later access SUSE "
"Multi-Linux Manager Server with a hostname that contains the fully qualified "
"domain name (\"FQDN\")!"
msgstr ""
"Debe configurar la red para que sus nodos periféricos puedan acceder "
"posteriormente a SUSE Multi-Linux Manager Server con un nombre de host que "
"contenga el nombre de dominio completo."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:450
msgid ""
"When you boot SUSE Multi-Linux Manager for the first time you need to "
"perform some initial configuration:"
msgstr ""
"Cuando inicie SUSE Multi-Linux Manager por primera vez, deberá realizar "
"algunas configuraciones iniciales:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:451
msgid "Select your keyboard layout"
msgstr "Seleccionar la disposición del teclado"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:452
msgid "Accept the license agreement"
msgstr "Aceptar el acuerdo de licencia"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:453
msgid "Select your time zone"
msgstr "Seleccionar la zona horaria"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:454
msgid "Enter the root password for the operating system"
msgstr "Introducir la contraseña raíz del sistema operativo"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:455
msgid "The next steps need to be done as the \"root\" user:"
msgstr "Los pasos siguientes se deben realizar con permisos de usuario root:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:456
msgid ""
"For the next step you need the registration code for the SUSE Multi-Linux "
"Manager Extension that you can find in the SUSE Customer Center. The same "
"code can be used for both registering SUSE Linux Micro and SUSE Multi-Linux "
"Manager:"
msgstr ""
"Para el paso siguiente, necesita el código de registro para la extensión de "
"SUSE Multi-Linux Manager que encontrará en el Centro de servicios al cliente "
"de SUSE. Se puede usar el mismo código para registrar tanto SUSE Linux Micro "
"como SUSE Multi-Linux Manager:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:457
msgid "Register SUSE Linux Micro:"
msgstr "Registre SUSE Linux Micro:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:458
msgid "Register SUSE Multi-Linux Manager:"
msgstr "Registre SUSE Multi-Linux Manager:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:459
msgid ""
"The product string depends on your hardware architecture! For example, if "
"you are using SUSE Multi-Linux Manager on a 64-bit Arm system, the string is "
"\"SUSE-Manager-Server/5.0/aarch64\"."
msgstr ""
"La cadena del producto depende de la arquitectura de su hardware. Por "
"ejemplo, si utiliza SUSE Multi-Linux Manager en un sistema ARM de 64 bits, "
"la cadena es \"SUSE-Manager-Server/5.0/aarch64\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:460
msgid "Reboot"
msgstr "Rearranque."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:461
msgid "Update the system:"
msgstr "Actualice el sistema:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:462
msgid "Unless there were no changes, reboot to apply the updates."
msgstr ""
"A menos que no haya habido cambios, reinicie el sistema para aplicar las "
"actualizaciones."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:463
msgid ""
"SUSE Multi-Linux Manager is provided via a container that is managed by "
"Podman. The <literal>mgradm</literal> command handles the setup and "
"configuration for you."
msgstr ""
"SUSE Multi-Linux Manager se proporciona a través de un contenedor gestionado "
"por Podman. El comando <literal>mgradm</literal> se encarga de la "
"instalación y la configuración."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><warning><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:464
msgid ""
"It is very important that your SUSE Multi-Linux Manager Server has the "
"hostname configured with a fully qualified domain name (\"FQDN\") that the "
"edge nodes you want to manage can properly resolve in your network!"
msgstr ""
"Es muy importante que el nombre de host configurado en su instancia de SUSE "
"Multi-Linux Manager Server tenga un nombre de dominio completo que los nodos "
"periféricos que desea administrar puedan resolver correctamente en su red."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:465
msgid ""
"Before you install and configure the SUSE Multi-Linux Manager Server "
"container, you need to prepare the additional block device that you have "
"previously added. For that, you need to know the name the virtual machine "
"has given to the device. For example, if the block device is <literal>/dev/"
"vdb</literal>, you can configure it to be used for SUSE Multi-Linux Manager "
"using the following command:"
msgstr ""
"Antes de instalar y configurar el contenedor de SUSE Multi-Linux Manager "
"Server, debe preparar el dispositivo de bloque adicional que ha añadido "
"previamente. Para ello, debe conocer el nombre que la máquina virtual ha "
"asignado al dispositivo. Por ejemplo, si el dispositivo de bloque es "
"<literal>/dev/vdb</literal>, puede configurarlo para que se utilice con SUSE "
"Multi-Linux Manager mediante el siguiente comando:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:466
msgid "Deploy SUSE Multi-Linux Manager:"
msgstr "Despliegue SUSE Multi-Linux Manager:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:467
msgid ""
"Provide the password for the CA certificate. This password should be "
"different from your login passwords. You usually don’t need to enter it "
"later, but you should note it down."
msgstr ""
"Proporcione la contraseña para el certificado de CA. Esta contraseña debe "
"ser diferente de sus contraseñas de inicio de sesión. Por lo general, no es "
"necesario introducirla más adelante, pero debe anotarla."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:468
msgid ""
"Provide the password for the \"admin\" user. This is the initial user for "
"logging into SUSE Multi-Linux Manager. You can create additional users with "
"full or restricted rights later."
msgstr ""
"Proporcione la contraseña para el usuario \"admin\". Se trata del usuario "
"inicial para iniciar sesión en SUSE Multi-Linux Manager. Más adelante podrá "
"crear usuarios adicionales con derechos completos o restringidos."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:469
msgid "Configure SUSE Multi-Linux Manager"
msgstr "Configuración de SUSE Multi-Linux Manager"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:470
msgid ""
"Once the deployment has finished, you can log into the SUSE Multi-Linux "
"Manager web UI using the host name you provided earlier. The initial user is "
"\"admin\". Use the password you provided in the previous step."
msgstr ""
"Una vez finalizado el despliegue, puede iniciar sesión en la interfaz de "
"usuario web de SUSE Multi-Linux Manager utilizando el nombre de host que "
"proporcionó anteriormente. El usuario inicial es \"admin\". Use la "
"contraseña que proporcionó en el paso anterior."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:471
msgid ""
"For the next step you need your Organization Credentials that you can find "
"on the 2nd sub-tab of the \"Users\" tab of your organization in SUSE "
"Customer Center. With those credentials, SUSE Multi-Linux Manager can "
"synchronize all the products that you have subscriptions for."
msgstr ""
"Para el siguiente paso, necesitará las credenciales de su organización, que "
"encontrará en la segunda subpestaña de la pestaña \"Usuarios\" de su "
"organización en el Centro de servicios al cliente de SUSE. Con esas "
"credenciales, SUSE Multi-Linux Manager puede sincronizar todos los productos "
"a los que está suscrito."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:472
msgid "Select <literal>Admin &gt; Setup Wizard</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Seleccione <literal>Administrador &gt; Asistente de configuración</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:473
msgid ""
"On the <literal>Organization Credentials</literal> tab create a new "
"credential with your <literal>Username</literal> and <literal>Password</"
"literal> that you found in the SUSE Customer Center."
msgstr ""
"En la pestaña <literal>Organization Credentials</literal> (Credenciales de "
"la organización) cree nuevas credenciales con sus datos de "
"<literal>Username</literal> (Nombre de usuario) y <literal>Password</"
"literal> (Contraseña) que encontró en el Centro de servicios al cliente de "
"SUSE."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:474
msgid ""
"Go to the next tab <literal>SUSE Products</literal>. You need to wait until "
"the first data synchronization with SUSE Customer Center has finished."
msgstr ""
"Diríjase a la pestaña siguiente, <literal>SUSE Products</literal> (Productos "
"SUSE). Debe esperar hasta que finalice la primera sincronización de datos "
"con el Centro de servicios al cliente de SUSE."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:475
msgid ""
"Once the list is populated, you use the filter to only show \"Micro 6.1\".  "
"Check the box for SUSE Linux Micro 6.1 for the hardware architecture your "
"edge nodes will run on (<literal>x86_64</literal> or <literal>aarch64</"
"literal>)."
msgstr ""
"Cuando la lista se haya rellenado, utilice el filtro para mostrar solo "
"\"Micro 6.1\". Marque la casilla de SUSE Linux Micro 6.1 para la "
"arquitectura de hardware en la que se ejecutarán sus nodos periféricos "
"(<literal>x86_64</literal> o <literal>aarch64</literal>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:476
msgid ""
"Click <literal>Add Products</literal>. This will add the main package "
"repository (\"channel\") for SUSE Linux Micro and automatically add the "
"channel for the SUSE Manager client tools as a sub-channel."
msgstr ""
"Haga clic en <literal>Add Products</literal> (Añadir productos). Esto "
"añadirá el repositorio de paquetes principal (\"canal\") para SUSE Linux "
"Micro y añadirá automáticamente el canal para las herramientas cliente de "
"SUSE Manager como un subcanal."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:477
msgid ""
"Depending on your Internet connection, the first synchronization will take a "
"while. You can already start with the next steps:"
msgstr ""
"Dependiendo de su conexión a Internet, la primera sincronización tardará un "
"poco. Ya puede empezar con los siguientes pasos:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:478
msgid ""
"Under <literal>Systems &gt; System Groups</literal>, create at least one "
"group that your systems will automatically join when they are onboarded. "
"Groups are an important way of categorizing systems, so you can apply "
"configuration or actions to a whole set of systems at once. They are "
"conceptionally similar to labels in Kubernetes."
msgstr ""
"En <literal>Systems &gt; System Groups</literal> (Sistemas > Grupos de "
"sistemas), cree al menos un grupo al que sus sistemas se unirán "
"automáticamente cuando se incorporen. Los grupos son una forma importante de "
"categorizar los sistemas, ya que permiten aplicar configuraciones o acciones "
"a un conjunto completo de sistemas a la vez. Conceptualmente, son similares "
"a las etiquetas de Kubernetes."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:479
msgid "Click <literal>+ Create Group</literal>"
msgstr "Haga clic en <literal>+ Create Group</literal> (Crear grupo)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:480
msgid "Provide a short name, e.g., \"Edge Nodes\", and long description."
msgstr ""
"Proporcione un nombre corto, por ejemplo, \"Nodos periféricos\", y una "
"descripción detallada."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:481
msgid ""
"Under <literal>Systems &gt; Activation Keys</literal>, create at least one "
"activation key. Activation keys can be thought of as a configuration profile "
"that is automatically applied to systems when they are onboarded to SUSE "
"Multi-Linux Manager. If you want certain edge nodes to be added to different "
"groups or use different configuration, you can create separate activation "
"keys for them and use them later in Edge Image Builder to create customized "
"installation media."
msgstr ""
"En <literal>Systems &gt; Activation Keys</literal> (Sistemas > Claves de "
"activación), cree al menos una clave de activación. Las claves de activación "
"pueden considerarse como un perfil de configuración que se aplica "
"automáticamente a los sistemas cuando se incorporan a SUSE Multi-Linux "
"Manager. Si desea que determinados nodos periféricos se añadan a diferentes "
"grupos o usen una configuración diferente, puede crear claves de activación "
"independientes para ellos y utilizarlas posteriormente en Edge Image Builder "
"para crear medios de instalación personalizados."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:482
msgid ""
"A typical advanced use case for activation keys would be to assign your test "
"clusters to the software channels with the latest updates and your "
"production clusters to software channels that only get those latest updates "
"once you’ve tested them in the test cluster."
msgstr ""
"Un caso de uso avanzado típico de las claves de activación sería asignar los "
"clústeres de prueba a los canales de software con las últimas "
"actualizaciones y los clústeres de producción a los canales de software que "
"solo reciben esas últimas actualizaciones una vez que se han probado en el "
"clúster de prueba."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:483
msgid "Click <literal>+ Create Key</literal>"
msgstr "Haga clic en <literal>+ Create Key</literal> (Crear clave)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:484
msgid ""
"Choose a short description, e.g., \"Edge Nodes\".  Provide a unique name "
"that identifies the key, e.g., \"edge-x86_64\" for your edge nodes with "
"AMD64/Intel 64 hardware architecture.  A number prefix is automatically "
"added to the key. For the default organization, the number is always \"1\". "
"If you create additional organizations in SUSE Multi-Linux Manager and "
"create keys for them, that number may differ."
msgstr ""
"Elija una descripción corta, por ejemplo, \"Nodos periféricos\". Proporcione "
"un nombre único que identifique la clave, por ejemplo, \"edge-x86_64\" para "
"sus nodos periféricos con arquitectura de hardware AMD64/Intel 64. Se añade "
"automáticamente un prefijo numérico a la clave. Para la organización "
"predeterminada, el número es siempre \"1\". Si crea organizaciones "
"adicionales en SUSE Multi-Linux Manager y crea claves para ellas, ese número "
"puede ser diferente."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:485
msgid ""
"If you haven’t created any cloned software channels, you can keep the "
"setting for the Base Channel to \"SUSE Manager Default\". This will "
"automatically assign the correct SUSE update repository for your edge nodes."
msgstr ""
"Si no ha creado ningún canal de software duplicado, puede conservar la "
"configuración del canal base como \"SUSE Manager Default\" (Predeterminada "
"de SUSE Manager). De este modo, se asignará automáticamente el repositorio "
"de actualizaciones de SUSE adecuado para sus nodos periféricos."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:486
msgid ""
"As \"Child Channel\", select the \"include recommended\" slider for the "
"hardware architecture your activation key is used for. This will add the "
"\"SUSE-Manager-Tools-For-SL-Micro-6.1\" channel."
msgstr ""
"Como \"Child Channel\" (Canal secundario), seleccione el control deslizante "
"\"Include recommended\" (Incluir recomendados) para la arquitectura de "
"hardware para la que se utiliza su clave de activación. Esto añadirá el "
"canal \"SUSE-Manager-Tools-For-SL-Micro-6.1\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:487
msgid ""
"On the \"Groups\" tab, add the group you’ve created before. All nodes that "
"are onboarded using this activation key will automatically be added to that "
"group."
msgstr ""
"En la pestaña \"Groups\" (Grupos), añada el grupo que ha creado "
"anteriormente. Todos los nodos que se incorporen utilizando esta clave de "
"activación se añadirán automáticamente a ese grupo."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:488
msgid "Create a customized installation image with Edge Image Builder"
msgstr ""
"Creación de una imagen de instalación personalizada con Edge Image Builder"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:489
msgid ""
"To use Edge Image Builder, you only need an environment where you can start "
"a Linux-based container with podman."
msgstr ""
"Para usar Edge Image Builder, solo necesita un entorno en el que pueda "
"iniciar un contenedor basado en Linux con Podman."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:490
msgid ""
"For a minimal lab setup, we can actually use the same virtual machine SUSE "
"Multi-Linux Manager Server is running on. Please make sure that you have "
"enough disk space in the virtual machine! This is not a recommended setup "
"for production use. See <xref linkend=\"id-prerequisites-2\"/> for host "
"operating systems we have tested Edge Image Builder with."
msgstr ""
"Para una configuración mínima del laboratorio, es posible usar la misma "
"máquina virtual en la que se ejecuta SUSE Multi-Linux Manager Server. "
"Asegúrese de que dispone de suficiente espacio en disco en la máquina "
"virtual. Esta configuración no es recomendable en entornos de producción. "
"Consulte la <xref linkend=\"id-prerequisites-2\"/> para conocer los sistemas "
"operativos host con los que hemos probado Edge Image Builder."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:491
msgid "Log into your SUSE Multi-Linux Manager Server host as root."
msgstr ""
"Inicie sesión en su host de SUSE Multi-Linux Manager Server como usuario "
"root."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:492
msgid "Pull the Edge Image Builder container:"
msgstr "Extraiga el contenedor de Edge Image Builder:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:493
msgid ""
"Create the directory <literal>/opt/eib</literal> and a sub-directory "
"<literal>base-images</literal>:"
msgstr ""
"Cree el directorio <literal>/opt/eib</literal> y un subdirectorio "
"<literal>base-images</literal>:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:494
msgid ""
"In this quickstart we’re using the \"self-install\" flavor of the SUSE Linux "
"Micro image. That image can later be written to a physical USB thumb drive "
"that you can use to install on physical servers. If your server has the "
"option of remote attachment of installation ISOs via a BMC (Baseboard "
"Management Controller), you can also use that approach. Finally that image "
"can also be used with most virtualization tools."
msgstr ""
"En esta guía de inicio rápido se usa la versión \"autoinstalable\" de la "
"imagen de SUSE Linux Micro. Esa imagen se puede grabar posteriormente en una "
"unidad USB física y utilizarse para la instalación en servidores físicos. Si "
"su servidor tiene la opción de conexión remota de imágenes ISO de "
"instalación a través de un BMC (Baseboard Management Controller), también "
"puede utilizar ese método. Por último, esa imagen también se puede utilizar "
"con la mayoría de las herramientas de virtualización."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:495
msgid ""
"If you either want to preload the image directly to a physical node or "
"directly start it from a VM, you can also use the \"raw\" image flavor."
msgstr ""
"Si desea precargar la imagen directamente en un nodo físico o iniciarla "
"directamente desde una máquina virtual, también puede utilizar el tipo de "
"imagen \"raw\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:496
msgid ""
"You can find those images in the SUSE Customer Center or on <link "
"xl:href=\"https://www.suse.com/download/sle-micro/\">https://www.suse.com/"
"download/sle-micro/</link>"
msgstr ""
"Encontrará esas imágenes en el Centro de servicios al cliente de SUSE o en "
"<link xl:href=\"https://www.suse.com/download/sle-micro/\">https://"
"www.suse.com/download/sle-micro/</link>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:497
msgid ""
"Download or copy the image <literal>SL-Micro.x86_64-6.1-Default-SelfInstall-"
"GM.install.iso</literal> to the <literal>base-images</literal> directoy and "
"name it \"slemicro.iso\"."
msgstr ""
"Descargue o copie la imagen <literal>SL-Micro.x86_64-6.1-Default-SelfInstall-"
"GM.install.iso</literal> en el directorio <literal>base-images</literal> y "
"asígnele el nombre \"slemicro.iso\"."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:498
msgid ""
"Building AArch64 images on an Arm-based build host is a technology preview "
"in SUSE Edge 3.4. It will most likely work, but isn’t supported yet. If you "
"want to try it out, you need to be running Podman on a 64-bit Arm machine, "
"and you need to replace \"x86_64\" in all the examples and code snippets "
"with \"aarch64\"."
msgstr ""
"La creación de imágenes AArch64 en un host de creación basado en ARM es una "
"tecnología en fase preliminar en SUSE Edge 3.4. Es muy probable que "
"funcione, pero aún no es compatible. Si desea probarlo, debe ejecutar Podman "
"en un equipo ARM de 64 bits y sustituir \"x86_64\" por \"aarch64\" en todos "
"los ejemplos y fragmentos de código."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:499
msgid ""
"In <literal>/opt/eib</literal>, create a file called <literal>iso-"
"definition.yaml</literal>. This is your build definition for Edge Image "
"Builder."
msgstr ""
"En <literal>/opt/eib</literal>, cree un archivo llamado <literal>iso-"
"definition.yaml</literal>. Esta es tu definición de creación para Edge Image "
"Builder."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:500
msgid ""
"Here is a simple example that installs SL Micro 6.1, sets a root password "
"and the keymap, starts the Cockpit graphical UI and registers your node to "
"SUSE Multi-Linux Manager:"
msgstr ""
"En este sencillo ejemplo se instala SL Micro 6.1, se establece una "
"contraseña raíz y el mapa de teclas, se inicia la interfaz gráfica Cockpit y "
"se registra el nodo en SUSE Multi-Linux Manager:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:501
msgid ""
"Edge Image Builder can also configure the network, automatically install "
"Kubernetes on the node, and even deploy applications via Helm charts. See "
"<xref linkend=\"quickstart-eib\"/> for more comprehensive examples."
msgstr ""
"Edge Image Builder también puede configurar la red, instalar automáticamente "
"Kubernetes en el nodo e, incluso, desplegar aplicaciones a través de charts "
"de Helm. Consulte el <xref linkend=\"quickstart-eib\"/> para obtener "
"ejemplos más completos."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:502
msgid ""
"For <literal>baseImage</literal>, specify the actual name of the ISO in the "
"<literal>base-images</literal> directory that you want to use."
msgstr ""
"Para <literal>baseImage</literal>, especifique el nombre real de la ISO en "
"el directorio <literal>base-images</literal> que desea utilizar."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:503
msgid ""
"In this example, the root password would be \"root\". See <xref linkend=\"id-"
"configuring-os-users\"/> for creating password hashes for the secure "
"password you want to use."
msgstr ""
"En este ejemplo, la contraseña raíz sería \"root\". Consulte la <xref "
"linkend=\"id-configuring-os-users\"/> para crear hashes para la contraseña "
"segura que desea utilizar."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:504
msgid ""
"Set the keymap to the actual keyboard layout you want the system to have "
"after installation."
msgstr ""
"Defina el mapa de teclas de la disposición de teclado actual que desee que "
"tenga el sistema después de la instalación."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:505
msgid ""
"We use the option <literal>noGPGCheck: true</literal> because we aren’t "
"going to provide a GPG key to check RPM packages. A comprehensive guide with "
"a more secure setup that we recommend for production use can be found in the "
"<link xl:href=\"https://github.com/suse-edge/edge-image-builder/blob/"
"release-1.3/docs/installing-packages.md\">upstream installing packages "
"guide</link>."
msgstr ""
"Utilizamos la opción <literal>noGPGCheck: true</literal> porque no vamos a "
"proporcionar una clave GPG para comprobar los paquetes RPM. En la <link "
"xl:href=\"https://github.com/suse-edge/edge-image-builder/blob/release-1.3/"
"docs/installing-packages.md\">guía original sobre instalación de paquetes</"
"link> encontrará instrucciones completas para realizar una configuración más "
"segura, que se recomienda en entornos de producción."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:506
msgid ""
"As mentioned several times, your SUSE Multi-Linux Manager host requires a "
"fully qualified hostname that can be resolved in the network your edge nodes "
"will boot into."
msgstr ""
"Como se ha mencionado en varias ocasiones, el host de SUSE Multi-Linux "
"Manager requiere un nombre de host completo que pueda resolverse en la red "
"en la que se iniciarán los nodos periféricos."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:507
msgid ""
"The value for <literal>activationKey</literal> needs to match the key you "
"created in SUSE Multi-Linux Manager."
msgstr ""
"El valor de <literal>activationKey</literal> debe coincidir con la clave que "
"ha creado en SUSE Multi-Linux Manager."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:508
msgid ""
"To build an installation image that automatically registers your edge nodes "
"to SUSE Multi-Linux Manager after installation, you also need to prepare two "
"artifacts:"
msgstr ""
"Para crear una imagen de instalación que registre automáticamente sus nodos "
"periféricos en SUSE Multi-Linux Manager después de la instalación, también "
"debe preparar dos artefactos:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:509
msgid ""
"the Salt minion package that installs the management agent for SUSE Multi-"
"Linux Manager"
msgstr ""
"El paquete minion de Salt que instala el agente de gestión para SUSE Multi-"
"Linux Manager"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:510
msgid "the CA certificate of your SUSE Multi-Linux Manager server"
msgstr ""
"El certificado de CA de su instancia de SUSE Multi-Linux Manager Server"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:511
msgid "Download the venv-salt-minion package"
msgstr "Descarga del paquete venv-salt-minion"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:512
msgid ""
"In <literal>/opt/eib</literal>, create a subdirectory <literal>rpms</"
"literal>."
msgstr ""
"En <literal>/opt/eib</literal>, cree un subdirectorio <literal>rpms</"
"literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:513
msgid ""
"Download the package <literal>venv-salt-minion</literal> from your SUSE "
"Multi-Linux Manager server into that directory. You can either get it via "
"the web UI by finding the package under <literal>Software &gt; Channel List</"
"literal> and downloading it from the SUSE-Manager-Tools …​ channel or "
"download it from the SUSE Multi-Linux Manager \"bootstrap repo\" with a tool "
"like curl:"
msgstr ""
"Descargue el paquete <literal>venv-salt-minion</literal> desde su instancia "
"de SUSE Multi-Linux Manager Server en ese directorio. Puede obtenerlo a "
"través de la interfaz de usuario web buscando el paquete en "
"<literal>Software &gt; Channel List</literal> (Software > Lista de canales) "
"y descargándolo desde el canal SUSE-Manager-Tools​, o bien descargarlo desde "
"el repositorio de arranque de SUSE Multi-Linux Manager con una herramienta "
"como curl:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:514
msgid ""
"The actual package name may differ if a newer release has already been "
"released. If there are multiple packages to choose from, always pick the "
"latest."
msgstr ""
"El nombre real del paquete puede variar si ya se ha lanzado una versión más "
"reciente. Si hay varios paquetes entre los que elegir, elija siempre el más "
"reciente."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:515
msgid ""
"To work around an issue documented in the <link xl:href=\"https://"
"www.suse.com/releasenotes/x86_64/multi-linux-manager/5.1/"
"index.html#_bootstrapping_sl_micro_6_1_clients\">release notes</link> for "
"SUSE Multi-Linux Manager, you also need to put the latest version of the "
"build key package into the <literal>rpms</literal> directory (<literal>suse-"
"build-key-12.0-slfo.1.1_3.1.noarch.rpm</literal> at the time this "
"documentation was created). You can find it in the <literal>Software</"
"literal> section of SUSE Multi-Linux Manager via the <literal>Packages</"
"literal> tab of the Pool channel of SL Micro. There is a <literal>Download</"
"literal> button in the <literal>Details</literal> view."
msgstr ""
"Como solución a un problema documentado en las <link xl:href=\"https://"
"www.suse.com/releasenotes/x86_64/multi-linux-manager/5.1/"
"index.html#_bootstrapping_sl_micro_6_1_clients\">notas de la versión</link> "
"de SUSE Multi-Linux Manager, también debe colocar la versión más reciente "
"del paquete de clave de versión en el directorio <literal>rpms</literal> "
"(<literal>suse-build-key-12.0-slfo.1.1_3.1.noarch.rpm</literal> cuando se "
"creó esta documentación). La encontrará en la sección <literal>Software</"
"literal> de SUSE Multi-Linux Manager, en la pestaña <literal>Paquetes</"
"literal> del canal Grupo de SL Micro. Hay un botón <literal>Descargar</"
"literal> en la vista <literal>Detalles</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:516
msgid "Download the SUSE Multi-Linux Manager CA certificate"
msgstr "Descarga del certificado de CA de SUSE Multi-Linux Manager"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:517
msgid ""
"In <literal>/opt/eib</literal>, create a subdirectory <literal>certificates</"
"literal>"
msgstr ""
"En <literal>/opt/eib</literal>, cree un subdirectorio <literal>certificates</"
"literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:518
msgid ""
"Download the CA certificate from SUSE Multi-Linux Manager into that "
"directory:"
msgstr ""
"Descargue el certificado de CA de SUSE Multi-Linux Manager en ese directorio:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><warning><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:519
msgid ""
"You have to rename the certificate to <literal>RHN-ORG-TRUSTED-SSL-CERT.crt</"
"literal>. Edge Image Builder will then make sure that the certificate is "
"installed and activated on the edge node during installation."
msgstr ""
"Debe cambiar el nombre del certificado a <literal>RHN-ORG-TRUSTED-SSL-"
"CERT.crt</literal>. Edge Image Builder se asegurará de que el certificado se "
"instale y se active en el nodo periférico durante la instalación."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:520
msgid "Now you can run Edge Image Builder:"
msgstr "Ahora puede ejecutar Edge Image Builder:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:521
msgid ""
"If you have used a different name for your YAML definition file or want to "
"use a different version of Edge Image Builder, you need to adapt the command "
"accordingly."
msgstr ""
"Si ha usado un nombre diferente para su archivo de definición YAML o desea "
"utilizar una versión diferente de Edge Image Builder, deberá adaptar el "
"comando en consecuencia."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:522
msgid ""
"After the build is finished, you’ll find the installation ISO in the "
"<literal>/opt/eib</literal> directory as <literal>eib-image.iso</literal>."
msgstr ""
"Una vez finalizada la creación, encontrará la imagen ISO de instalación en "
"el directorio <literal>/opt/eib</literal> con el nombre <literal>eib-"
"image.iso</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:523
msgid ""
"That image can now be used to deploy nodes that will try to register with "
"SUSE Multi-Linux Manager."
msgstr ""
"Esa imagen se puede usar ahora para desplegar nodos que intentarán "
"registrarse con SUSE Multi-Linux Manager."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:524
msgid ""
"After the node has fully installed, you will see its key listed as "
"<literal>pending</literal> in the <literal>Salt/Keys</literal> section of "
"SUSE Multi-Linux Manager. Once you have accepted the key, the node will "
"automatically be onboarded to SUSE Multi-Liux Manager and show up in the "
"<literal>Systems</literal> list after that process is finished. It will have "
"the system group(s) assigned that you provided in the activation key."
msgstr ""
"Después de que los nodos se hayan instalado por completo, verá su clave como "
"<literal>pendiente</literal> en la sección <literal>Salt/Keys</literal> de "
"SUSE Multi-Linux Manager. Cuando haya aceptado la clave, el nodo se "
"incorporará automáticamente a SUSE Multi-Liux Manager y se mostrará en la "
"lista <literal>Sistemas</literal> después de que finalice el proceso. Tendrá "
"asignados los grupos del sistema que haya proporcionado en la clave de "
"activación."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:525
msgid ""
"You should then schedule a reboot before applying any additional "
"configuration."
msgstr ""
"A continuación, debe programar un rearranque antes de aplicar cualquier "
"configuración adicional."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:526
msgid ""
"Note that accepting the key can be fully automated using whitelists as "
"described <link xl:href=\"https://docs.saltproject.io/en/latest/topics/"
"tutorials/autoaccept_grains.html\">here</link>."
msgstr ""
"La aceptación de la clave se puede automatizar mediantes listas de "
"permitidos, como se describe <link xl:href=\"https://docs.saltproject.io/en/"
"latest/topics/tutorials/autoaccept_grains.html\">aquí</link>."

