#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1282 l10n/source/edge.xml:1329
msgid "Why use MetalLB"
msgstr "Por qué usar MetalLB"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1283 l10n/source/edge.xml:1330
msgid ""
"MetalLB is a compelling choice for load balancing in bare-metal Kubernetes "
"clusters for several reasons:"
msgstr ""
"MetalLB es una opción conveniente para el equilibrio de carga en clústeres "
"bare metal de Kubernetes por varias razones:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1284 l10n/source/edge.xml:1331
msgid ""
"Native Integration with Kubernetes: MetalLB seamlessly integrates with "
"Kubernetes, making it easy to deploy and manage using familiar Kubernetes "
"tools and practices."
msgstr ""
"Integración nativa con Kubernetes: MetalLB se integra a la perfección con "
"Kubernetes, lo que facilita el despliegue y la gestión mediante las "
"herramientas y prácticas habituales de Kubernetes."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1285 l10n/source/edge.xml:1332
msgid ""
"Bare-Metal Compatibility: Unlike cloud-based load balancers, MetalLB is "
"designed specifically for on-premises deployments where traditional load "
"balancers might not be available or feasible."
msgstr ""
"Compatibilidad bare metal: a diferencia de los equilibradores de carga "
"basados en la nube, MetalLB se ha diseñado específicamente para despliegues "
"locales en las que los sistemas de equilibrio de carga tradicionales podrían "
"no estar disponibles o no ser viables."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1286
msgid ""
"Supports Multiple Protocols: MetalLB supports both Layer 2 and BGP (Border "
"Gateway Protocol) modes, providing flexibility for different network "
"architectures and requirements."
msgstr ""
"Compatibilidad con múltiples protocolos: MetalLB admite el modo de capa 2 y "
"BGP (Border Gateway Protocol, protocolo de gateway de frontera), lo que "
"proporciona flexibilidad para diferentes arquitecturas y requisitos de red."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1287 l10n/source/edge.xml:1334
msgid ""
"High Availability: By distributing load-balancing responsibilities across "
"multiple nodes, MetalLB ensures high availability and reliability for your "
"services."
msgstr ""
"Alta disponibilidad: dado que distribuye el equilibrio de carga entre varios "
"nodos, MetalLB garantiza una alta disponibilidad y fiabilidad para sus "
"servicios."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1288 l10n/source/edge.xml:1335
msgid ""
"Scalability: MetalLB can handle large-scale deployments, scaling alongside "
"your Kubernetes cluster to meet increasing demand."
msgstr ""
"Escalabilidad: MetalLB puede manejar despliegues a gran escala, y se va "
"adaptando con su clúster de Kubernetes para satisfacer la demanda creciente."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1289 l10n/source/edge.xml:1336
msgid ""
"In layer 2 mode, one node assumes the responsibility of advertising a "
"service to the local network. From the network’s perspective, it simply "
"looks like that machine has multiple IP addresses assigned to its network "
"interface."
msgstr ""
"En el modo de capa 2 (L2), un nodo asume la responsabilidad de anunciar un "
"servicio a la red local. Desde la perspectiva de la red, simplemente parece "
"que esa máquina tiene varias direcciones IP asignadas a su interfaz de red."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1290 l10n/source/edge.xml:1337
msgid ""
"The major advantage of the layer 2 mode is its universality: it works on any "
"Ethernet network, with no special hardware required, not even fancy routers."
msgstr ""
"La mayor ventaja del modo de capa 2 es su universalidad: funciona en "
"cualquier red Ethernet sin necesidad de hardware especial, ni siquiera de "
"routers sofisticados."

