#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1831 l10n/source/edge.xml:2339
msgid ""
"The OS upgrade on a specific node is handled by a <link xl:href=\"https://"
"www.freedesktop.org/software/systemd/man/latest/"
"systemd.service.html\">systemd.service</link>."
msgstr ""
"La actualización del sistema operativo en un nodo específico se gestiona "
"mediante un servicio <link xl:href=\"https://www.freedesktop.org/software/"
"systemd/man/latest/systemd.service.html\">systemd.service</link>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1832 l10n/source/edge.xml:2340
msgid ""
"A different service is created depending on what type of upgrade the OS "
"requires from one Edge version to another:"
msgstr ""
"En función del tipo de actualización que requiera el sistema operativo de "
"una versión de Edge a otra, se creará un servicio diferente:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1833 l10n/source/edge.xml:2341
msgid ""
"For Edge versions that require the same OS version (e.g. <literal>6.0</"
"literal>), the <literal>os-pkg-update.service</literal> will be created. It "
"uses <link xl:href=\"https://kubic.opensuse.org/documentation/man-pages/"
"transactional-update.8.html\">transactional-update</link> to perform a <link "
"xl:href=\"https://en.opensuse.org/"
"SDB:Zypper_usage#Updating_packages\">normal package upgrade</link>."
msgstr ""
"Para las versiones de Edge que requieren la misma versión del sistema "
"operativo (por ejemplo, la <literal>6.0</literal>), se creará el servicio "
"<literal>os-pkg-update.service</literal>. Use <link xl:href=\"https://"
"kubic.opensuse.org/documentation/man-pages/transactional-"
"update.8.html\">transactional-update</link> para realizar una <link "
"xl:href=\"https://en.opensuse.org/"
"SDB:Zypper_usage#Updating_packages\">actualización normal del paquete</link>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1834 l10n/source/edge.xml:2342
msgid ""
"For Edge versions that require an OS version migration (e.g <literal>6.0</"
"literal> → <literal>6.1</literal>), the <literal>os-migration.service</"
"literal> will be created. It uses <link xl:href=\"https://kubic.opensuse.org/"
"documentation/man-pages/transactional-update.8.html\">transactional-update</"
"link> to perform:"
msgstr ""
"Para las versiones de Edge que requieran una migración de la versión del "
"sistema operativo (por ejemplo, de la <literal>6.0</literal> a la "
"<literal>6.1</literal>), se creará el servicio <literal>os-"
"migration.service</literal>. Use <link xl:href=\"https://kubic.opensuse.org/"
"documentation/man-pages/transactional-update.8.html\">transactional-update</"
"link> para realizar:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1835 l10n/source/edge.xml:2343
msgid ""
"A <link xl:href=\"https://en.opensuse.org/"
"SDB:Zypper_usage#Updating_packages\">normal package upgrade</link> which "
"ensures that all packages are at up-to-date in order to mitigate any "
"failures in the migration related to old package versions."
msgstr ""
"Una <link xl:href=\"https://en.opensuse.org/"
"SDB:Zypper_usage#Updating_packages\">actualización normal del paquete</link> "
"que garantice que todos los paquetes estén actualizados para mitigar "
"cualquier fallo en la migración relacionado con versiones antiguas del "
"paquete."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1836 l10n/source/edge.xml:2344
msgid ""
"An OS migration by utilizing the <literal>zypper migration</literal> command."
msgstr ""
"Una migración del sistema operativo mediante el comando <literal>zypper "
"migration</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1837
msgid ""
"The services mentioned above are shipped on each node through a <literal>SUC "
"plan</literal> which must be located on the management cluster that is in "
"need of an OS upgrade."
msgstr ""
"Los servicios mencionados anteriormente se envían a cada nodo a través de un "
"<literal>plan de SUC</literal>, que debe estar ubicado en el clúster de "
"gestión que necesita una actualización del sistema operativo."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1838 l10n/source/edge.xml:1956
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2191 l10n/source/edge.xml:2346
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2461 l10n/source/edge.xml:2687
msgid "Overview"
msgstr "Descripción general"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1839
msgid ""
"The upgrade of the operating system for management cluster nodes is done by "
"utilizing <literal>Fleet</literal> and the <literal>System Upgrade "
"Controller (SUC)</literal>."
msgstr ""
"La actualización del sistema operativo para los nodos del clúster de gestión "
"se realiza con <literal>Fleet</literal> y <literal>System Upgrade Controller "
"(SUC)</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1840 l10n/source/edge.xml:2348
msgid ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">Fleet</emphasis> is used to deploy and manage "
"<literal>SUC plans</literal> onto the desired cluster."
msgstr ""
"<emphasis role=\"strong\">Fleet</emphasis> se usa para desplegar y gestionar "
"<literal>planes de SUC</literal> en el clúster deseado."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1841 l10n/source/edge.xml:2349
msgid ""
"<literal>SUC plans</literal> are <link xl:href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/"
"concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/\">custom "
"resources</link> that describe the steps that <literal>SUC</literal> needs "
"to follow in order for a specific task to be executed on a set of nodes. For "
"an example of how an <literal>SUC plan</literal> looks like, refer to the "
"<link xl:href=\"https://github.com/rancher/system-upgrade-controller?"
"tab=readme-ov-file#example-plans\">upstream repository</link>."
msgstr ""
"Los <literal>planes de SUC</literal> son <link xl:href=\"https://"
"kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/extend-kubernetes/api-extension/custom-resources/"
"\">recursos personalizados</link> que describen los pasos que debe seguir "
"<literal>SUC</literal> para ejecutar una tarea específica en un conjunto de "
"nodos. Para ver un ejemplo de cómo es un <literal>plan de SUC</literal>, "
"consulte el <link xl:href=\"https://github.com/rancher/system-upgrade-"
"controller?tab=readme-ov-file#example-plans\">repositorio original</link>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1842 l10n/source/edge.xml:2350
msgid ""
"The <literal>OS SUC plans</literal> are shipped to each cluster by deploying "
"a <link xl:href=\"https://fleet.rancher.io/gitrepo-add\">GitRepo</link> or "
"<link xl:href=\"https://fleet.rancher.io/bundle-add\">Bundle</link> resource "
"to a specific Fleet <link xl:href=\"https://fleet.rancher.io/"
"namespaces#gitrepos-bundles-clusters-clustergroups\">workspace</link>. Fleet "
"retrieves the deployed <literal>GitRepo/Bundle</literal> and deploys its "
"contents (the <literal>OS SUC plans</literal>) to the desired cluster(s)."
msgstr ""
"Los <literal>planes de SUC de sistema operativo</literal> se envían a cada "
"clúster desplegando un recurso <link xl:href=\"https://fleet.rancher.io/"
"gitrepo-add\">GitRepo</link> o <link xl:href=\"https://fleet.rancher.io/"
"bundle-add\">Bundle</link> a un <link xl:href=\"https://fleet.rancher.io/"
"namespaces#gitrepos-bundles-clusters-clustergroups\">espacio de trabajo</"
"link> de Fleet específico. Fleet recupera el <literal>GitRepo/Bundle</"
"literal> desplegado y despliega su contenido (los <literal>planes de SUC de "
"sistema operativo</literal>) en los clústeres deseados."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1843 l10n/source/edge.xml:1961
msgid ""
"<literal>GitRepo/Bundle</literal> resources are always deployed on the "
"<literal>management cluster</literal>. Whether to use a <literal>GitRepo</"
"literal> or <literal>Bundle</literal> resource depends on your use-case, "
"check <xref linkend=\"management-day2-fleet-determine-use-case\"/> for more "
"information."
msgstr ""
"Los recursos <literal>GitRepo/Bundle</literal> siempre se despliegan en el "
"<literal>clúster de gestión</literal>. Que se use un recurso "
"<literal>GitRepo</literal> o <literal>Bundle</literal> depende del caso de "
"uso. Consulte la <xref linkend=\"management-day2-fleet-determine-use-case\"/"
"> para obtener más información."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1844 l10n/source/edge.xml:2352
msgid "<literal>OS SUC plans</literal> describe the following workflow:"
msgstr ""
"Los <literal>planes de SUC de sistema operativo</literal> describen el "
"siguiente flujo de trabajo:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1845 l10n/source/edge.xml:2353
msgid ""
"Always <link xl:href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/kubectl/"
"generated/kubectl_cordon/\">cordon</link> the nodes before OS upgrades."
msgstr ""
"Use siempre el comando <link xl:href=\"https://kubernetes.io/docs/reference/"
"kubectl/generated/kubectl_cordon/\">cordon</link> en los nodos antes de las "
"actualizaciones del sistema operativo."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1846 l10n/source/edge.xml:1964
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2354 l10n/source/edge.xml:2469
msgid ""
"Always upgrade <literal>control-plane</literal> nodes before "
"<literal>worker</literal> nodes."
msgstr ""
"Actualice siempre los nodos <literal>control-plane</literal> antes que los "
"nodos <literal>worker</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1847 l10n/source/edge.xml:2355
msgid ""
"Always upgrade the cluster on a <emphasis role=\"strong\">one</emphasis> "
"node at a time basis."
msgstr ""
"Actualice siempre el clúster en un <emphasis role=\"strong\">único</"
"emphasis> nodo cada vez."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1848 l10n/source/edge.xml:2356
msgid ""
"Once the <literal>OS SUC plans</literal> are deployed, the workflow looks "
"like this:"
msgstr ""
"Una vez desplegados los <literal>planes de SUC de sistema operativo</"
"literal>, el flujo de trabajo es el siguiente:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1849 l10n/source/edge.xml:2357
msgid ""
"SUC reconciles the deployed <literal>OS SUC plans</literal> and creates a "
"<literal>Kubernetes Job</literal> on <emphasis role=\"strong\">each node</"
"emphasis>."
msgstr ""
"SUC reconcilia los <literal>planes de SUC de sistema operativo</literal> "
"desplegados y crea un <literal>trabajo de Kubernetes</literal> en <emphasis "
"role=\"strong\">cada nodo</emphasis>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1850
msgid ""
"The <literal>Kubernetes Job</literal> creates a systemd.service (<xref "
"linkend=\"management-day2-fleet-os-upgrade-components-systemd-service\"/>) "
"for either package upgrade, or OS migration."
msgstr ""
"El <literal>trabajo de Kubernetes</literal> crea un servicio systemd.service "
"(<xref linkend=\"management-day2-fleet-os-upgrade-components-systemd-"
"service\"/>) para la actualización de paquetes o para la migración del "
"sistema operativo."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1851 l10n/source/edge.xml:2359
msgid ""
"The created <literal>systemd.service</literal> triggers the OS upgrade "
"process on the specific node."
msgstr ""
"El servicio <literal>systemd.service</literal> creado activa el proceso de "
"actualización del sistema operativo en el nodo específico."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><orderedlist><listitem><important><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1852 l10n/source/edge.xml:2360
msgid ""
"Once the OS upgrade process finishes, the corresponding node will be "
"<literal>rebooted</literal> to apply the updates on the system."
msgstr ""
"Cuando finaliza el proceso de actualización del sistema operativo, el nodo "
"correspondiente se <literal>rearranca</literal> para aplicar las "
"actualizaciones en el sistema."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:1853 l10n/source/edge.xml:1973
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2204 l10n/source/edge.xml:2361
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:2478 l10n/source/edge.xml:2700
