#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3049
msgid "Setting up the management cluster"
msgstr "Configuración del clúster de gestión"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3051
msgid ""
"The management cluster is the part of SUSE Telco Cloud that is used to "
"manage the provision and lifecycle of the runtime stacks.  From a technical "
"point of view, the management cluster contains the following components:"
msgstr ""
"El clúster de gestión es la parte de SUSE Telco Cloud que se emplea para "
"gestionar el aprovisionamiento y el ciclo de vida de las pilas de entorno de "
"ejecución. Desde un punto de vista técnico, el clúster de gestión contiene "
"los componentes siguientes:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3052
msgid ""
"<literal>SUSE Linux Micro</literal> as the OS. Depending on the use case, "
"some configurations like networking, storage, users and kernel arguments can "
"be customized."
msgstr ""
"<literal>SUSE Linux Micro</literal> como sistema operativo. Dependiendo del "
"caso práctico, será posible personalizar algunas configuraciones como la "
"red, el almacenamiento, los usuarios y los argumentos del kernel."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3053
msgid ""
"<literal>RKE2</literal> as the Kubernetes cluster. Depending on the use "
"case, it can be configured to use specific CNI plugins, such as "
"<literal>Multus</literal>, <literal>Cilium</literal>, <literal>Calico</"
"literal>, etc."
msgstr ""
"<literal>RKE2</literal> como clúster de Kubernetes. Dependiendo del caso "
"práctico, se puede configurar para utilizar complementos de CNI específicos, "
"como <literal>Multus</literal>, <literal>Cilium</literal>, <literal>Calico</"
"literal>, etc."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3054
msgid ""
"<literal>Rancher</literal> as the management platform to manage the "
"lifecycle of the clusters."
msgstr ""
"<literal>Rancher</literal> como plataforma de gestión del ciclo de vida de "
"los clústeres."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3055
msgid ""
"<literal>Metal<superscript>3</superscript></literal> as the component to "
"manage the lifecycle of the bare-metal nodes."
msgstr ""
"<literal>Metal<superscript>3</superscript></literal> como componente para "
"gestionar el ciclo de vida de los nodos bare metal."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3056
msgid ""
"<literal>CAPI</literal> as the component to manage the lifecycle of the "
"Kubernetes clusters (downstream clusters). The <literal>RKE2 CAPI Provider</"
"literal> is used to manage the lifecycle of the RKE2 clusters."
msgstr ""
"<literal>CAPI</literal> como componente para gestionar el ciclo de vida de "
"los clústeres de Kubernetes (clústeres descendentes). El <literal>proveedor "
"CAPI de RKE2</literal> se utiliza para gestionar el ciclo de vida de los "
"clústeres RKE2."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3057
msgid ""
"With all components mentioned above, the management cluster can manage the "
"lifecycle of downstream clusters, using a declarative approach to manage the "
"infrastructure and applications."
msgstr ""
"Con todos los componentes mencionados, el clúster de gestión puede gestionar "
"el ciclo de vida de los clústeres descendentes usando un enfoque declarativo "
"para gestionar la infraestructura y las aplicaciones."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3058
msgid ""
"For more information about <literal>SUSE Linux Micro</literal>, see: SUSE "
"Linux Micro (<xref linkend=\"components-slmicro\"/>)"
msgstr ""
"Para obtener más información sobre <literal>SUSE Linux Micro</literal>, "
"consulte: SUSE Linux Micro (<xref linkend=\"components-slmicro\"/>)"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
