#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3568
msgid "Prepare downstream cluster image for connected scenarios"
msgstr ""
"Preparación de la imagen del clúster descendente para entornos conectados"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3569 l10n/source/edge.xml:3615
msgid ""
"Edge Image Builder (<xref linkend=\"components-eib\"/>) is used to prepare a "
"modified SLEMicro base image which is provisioned on downstream cluster "
"hosts."
msgstr ""
"Edge Image Builder (<xref linkend=\"components-eib\"/>) se utiliza para "
"preparar una imagen base de SLEMicro modificada que se aprovisiona en los "
"hosts del clúster descendente."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3570
msgid ""
"Much of the configuration via Edge Image Builder is possible, but in this "
"guide, we cover the minimal configurations necessary to set up the "
"downstream cluster."
msgstr ""
"Gran parte de la configuración se puede realizar con Edge Image Builder, "
"pero en esta guía cubrimos las configuraciones mínimas necesarias para "
"configurar el clúster descendente."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3571
msgid "Prerequisites for connected scenarios"
msgstr "Requisitos previos para entornos conectados"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3572 l10n/source/edge.xml:3618
msgid ""
"A container runtime such as <link xl:href=\"https://podman.io\">Podman</"
"link> or <link xl:href=\"https://rancherdesktop.io\">Rancher Desktop</link> "
"is required to run Edge Image Builder."
msgstr ""
"Se requiere un entorno de ejecución de contenedores como <link "
"xl:href=\"https://podman.io\">Podman</link> o <link xl:href=\"https://"
"rancherdesktop.io\">Rancher Desktop</link> para ejecutar Edge Image Builder."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3573 l10n/source/edge.xml:3619
msgid ""
"The base image will be built using the following guide <xref "
"linkend=\"guides-kiwi-builder-images\"/> with the profile <literal>Base-"
"SelfInstall</literal> (or <literal>Base-RT-SelfInstall</literal> for the "
"Real-Time kernel). The process is the same for both architectures (x86-64 "
"and aarch64)."
msgstr ""
"La imagen base se creará con las instrucciones del <xref linkend=\"guides-"
"kiwi-builder-images\"/> y el perfil <literal>Base-SelfInstall</literal> (o "
"<literal>Base-RT-SelfInstall</literal> para el kernel en tiempo real). El "
"proceso es el mismo para ambas arquitecturas (x86-64 y aarch64)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3574 l10n/source/edge.xml:3621
msgid ""
"It is required to use a build host with the same architecture of the images "
"being built. In other words, to build an <literal>aarch64</literal> image, "
"it is required to use an <literal>aarch64</literal> build host, and vice-"
"versa for <literal>x86-64</literal> (cross-builds are not supported at this "
"time)."
msgstr ""
"Es necesario utilizar un host de creación con la misma arquitectura que las "
"imágenes que se están creando. En otras palabras, para crear una imagen "
"<literal>aarch64</literal>, es necesario utilizar un host de creación "
"<literal>aarch64</literal>, y lo mismo ocurre para <literal>x86-64</literal> "
"(actualmente, no se admiten creaciones con arquitecturas cruzadas)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3575
msgid "Image configuration for connected scenarios"
msgstr "Configuración de la imagen para entornos conectados"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3578 l10n/source/edge.xml:3625
msgid ""
"The base image folder will contain the output raw image generated following "
"the guide <xref linkend=\"guides-kiwi-builder-images\"/> with the profile "
"<literal>Base-SelfInstall</literal> (or <literal>Base-RT-SelfInstall</"
"literal> for the Real-Time kernel) must be copied/moved under the "
"<literal>base-images</literal> folder."
msgstr ""
"La carpeta de imágenes base contendrá la imagen raw generada al seguir las "
"instrucciones del <xref linkend=\"guides-kiwi-builder-images\"/> con el "
"perfil <literal>Base-SelfInstall</literal> (o <literal>Base-RT-SelfInstall</"
"literal> para el kernel en tiempo real) y deberá copiarse/moverse a la "
"carpeta <literal>base-images</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3579 l10n/source/edge.xml:3626
msgid ""
"The <literal>network</literal> folder is optional, see <xref linkend=\"add-"
"network-eib\"/> for more details."
msgstr ""
"La carpeta <literal>network</literal> es opcional. Para obtener más "
"información, consulte la <xref linkend=\"add-network-eib\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3580 l10n/source/edge.xml:3627
msgid ""
"The <literal>custom/scripts</literal> directory contains scripts to be run "
"on first-boot:"
msgstr ""
"El directorio <literal>custom/scripts</literal> contiene guiones que se "
"deben ejecutar en el primer arranque:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3581
msgid ""
"<literal>01-fix-growfs.sh</literal> script is required to resize the OS root "
"partition on deployment"
msgstr ""
"El guion <literal>01-fix-growfs.sh</literal> es necesario para cambiar el "
"tamaño de la partición raíz del sistema operativo durante el despliegue."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3582
msgid ""
"<literal>02-performance.sh</literal> script is optional and can be used to "
"configure the system for performance tuning."
msgstr ""
"El guion <literal>02-performance.sh</literal> es opcional y se puede usar "
"para configurar el sistema con el fin de optimizar su rendimiento."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><orderedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3583
msgid ""
"<literal>03-sriov.sh</literal> script is optional and can be used to "
"configure the system for SR-IOV."
msgstr ""
"El guion <literal>03-sriov.sh</literal> es opcional y se puede usar para "
"configurar el sistema para SR-IOV."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3584
msgid ""
"The <literal>custom/files</literal> directory contains the "
"<literal>performance-settings.sh</literal> and <literal>sriov-auto-"
"filler.sh</literal> files to be copied to the image during the image "
"creation process."
msgstr ""
"El directorio <literal>custom/files</literal> contiene los archivos "
"<literal>performance-settings.sh</literal> y <literal>sriov-auto-filler.sh</"
"literal> que se copiarán en la imagen durante el proceso de creación de la "
"imagen."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3587
msgid ""
"Where <literal>$SCC_REGISTRATION_CODE</literal> is the registration code "
"copied from <link xl:href=\"https://scc.suse.com/\">SUSE Customer Center</"
"link>, and the package list contains <literal>jq</literal> which is required."
msgstr ""
"Donde <literal>$SCC_REGISTRATION_CODE</literal> es el código de registro "
"copiado del <link xl:href=\"https://scc.suse.com/\">Centro de servicios al "
"cliente de SUSE</link>, y la lista de paquetes contiene <literal>jq</"
"literal>, que es necesario."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3590 l10n/source/edge.xml:3606
msgid ""
"<literal>arch: x86_64</literal> is the architecture of the image. For arm64 "
"architecture, use <literal>arch: aarch64</literal>."
msgstr ""
"<literal>arch: x86_64</literal> es la arquitectura de la imagen. Para la "
"arquitectura arm64, utilice <literal>arch: aarch64</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><section><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3592
