"con formato <literal>nmstate</literal>. El siguiente archivo de ejemplo "
"define un secreto que contiene el bloque <literal>networkData</literal> "
"necesario que solicita una <literal>IP</literal> estática y una "
"<literal>VLAN</literal> para el host del clúster descendente:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3768
msgid ""
"As you can see, the example shows the configuration to enable the interface "
"with static IPs, as well as the configuration to enable the VLAN using the "
"base interface, once the following variables are replaced with the actual "
"values, according to your infrastructure:"
msgstr ""
"Como puede ver, el ejemplo muestra la configuración para habilitar la "
"interfaz con direcciones IP estáticas, así como la configuración para "
"habilitar la VLAN utilizando la interfaz base, una vez que las siguientes "
"variables se sustituyan por los valores reales de su infraestructura:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3769
msgid ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_INTERFACE}</literal> — The control-plane interface "
"to be used for the edge cluster (for example, <literal>eth0</literal>). "
"Including <literal>identifier: mac-address</literal> the naming is inspected "
"automatically by the MAC address so any interface name can be used."
msgstr ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_INTERFACE}</literal>: es la interfaz de plano de "
"control que se usará para el clúster periférico (por ejemplo, <literal>eth0</"
"literal>). Si se incluye <literal>identificador: dirección MAC</literal>, el "
"nombre se comprueba automáticamente por su dirección MAC, por lo que se "
"puede utilizar cualquier nombre de interfaz."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3770
msgid ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_IP}</literal> — The IP address to be used as an "
"endpoint for the edge cluster (must match with the kubeapi-server endpoint)."
msgstr ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_IP}</literal>: es la dirección IP que se usará como "
"punto final para el clúster periférico (debe coincidir con el punto final "
"kubeapi-server)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3771
msgid ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_PREFIX}</literal> — The CIDR to be used for the edge "
"cluster (for example, <literal>24</literal> if you want <literal>/24</"
"literal> or <literal>255.255.255.0</literal>)."
msgstr ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_PREFIX}</literal>: es el CIDR que se usará para el "
"clúster periférico (por ejemplo, <literal>24</literal> si desea <literal>/"
"24</literal> o <literal>255.255.255.0</literal>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3772
msgid ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_GATEWAY}</literal> — The gateway to be used for the "
"edge cluster (for example, <literal>192.168.100.1</literal>)."
msgstr ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_GATEWAY}</literal>: es el gateway que se usará para "
"el clúster periférico (por ejemplo, <literal>192.168.100.1</literal>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3773
msgid ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_MAC}</literal> — The MAC address to be used for the "
"control-plane interface (for example, <literal>00:0c:29:3e:3e:3e</literal>)."
msgstr ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_MAC}</literal>: es la dirección MAC que se usará "
"para la interfaz de plano de control (por ejemplo, "
"<literal>00:0c:29:3e:3e:3e</literal>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3774
msgid ""
"<literal>${DNS_SERVER}</literal> — The DNS to be used for the edge cluster "
"(for example, <literal>192.168.100.2</literal>)."
msgstr ""
"<literal>${DNS_SERVER}</literal>: es el servidor DNS que se usará para el "
"clúster periférico (por ejemplo, <literal>192.168.100.2</literal>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3775
msgid ""
"<literal>${VLAN_ID}</literal> — The VLAN ID to be used for the edge cluster "
"(for example, <literal>100</literal>)."
msgstr ""
"<literal>${VLAN_ID}</literal>: es el ID de VLAN que se usará para el clúster "
"periférico (por ejemplo, <literal>100</literal>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3776
msgid ""
"Any other <literal>nmstate</literal>-compliant definition can be used to "
"configure the network for the downstream cluster to adapt to the specific "
"requirements. For example, it is possible to specify a static dual-stack "
"configuration:"
msgstr ""
"Se puede usar cualquier otra definición compatible con <literal>nmstate</"
"literal> para configurar la red del clúster descendente y adaptarla a los "
"requisitos específicos. Por ejemplo, es posible especificar una "
"configuración estática de doble pila:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3777
msgid ""
"As for the previous example, replace the following variables with actual "
"values, according to your infrastructure:"
msgstr ""
"En el ejemplo anterior, sustituya las variables siguientes por los valores "
"reales de su infraestructura:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3778
msgid ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_IP_V4}</literal> - the IPv4 address to assign to the "
"host"
msgstr ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_IP_V4}</literal>: la dirección IPv4 que se asignará "
"al host"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3779
msgid ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_PREFIX_V4}</literal> - the IPv4 prefix of the "
"network to which the host IP belongs"
msgstr ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_PREFIX_V4}</literal>: el prefijo IPv4 de la red a la "
"que pertenece la IP del host"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3780
msgid ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_IP_V6}</literal> - the IPv6 address to assign to the "
"host"
msgstr ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_IP_V6}</literal>: la dirección IPv6 que se asignará "
"al host"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3781
msgid ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_PREFIX_V6}</literal> - the IPv6 prefix of the "
"network to which the host IP belongs"
msgstr ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_PREFIX_V6}</literal>: el prefijo IPv6 de la red a la "
"que pertenece la IP del host"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3782
msgid ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_GATEWAY_V4}</literal> - the IPv4 address of the "
"gateway for the traffic matching the default route"
msgstr ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_GATEWAY_V4}</literal>: la dirección IPv4 del gateway "
"para el tráfico que coincide con la ruta predeterminada"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3783
msgid ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_GATEWAY_V6}</literal> - the IPv6 address of the "
"gateway for the traffic matching the default route"
msgstr ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_GATEWAY_V6}</literal>: la dirección IPv6 del gateway "
"para el tráfico que coincide con la ruta predeterminada"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3784
msgid ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_INTERFACE}</literal> - the name of the interface to "
"assign the addresses to and to use for egress traffic matching the default "
"route, for both IPv4 and IPv6"
msgstr ""
"<literal>${CONTROLPLANE_INTERFACE}</literal>: el nombre de la interfaz a la "
"que se asignarán las direcciones y que se usará para el tráfico de salida "
"que coincida con la ruta predeterminada, tanto para IPv4 como para IPv6"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3785
msgid ""
"<literal>${DNS_SERVER_V4}</literal> and/or <literal>${DNS_SERVER_V6}</"
"literal> - the IP address(es) of the DNS server(s) to use, which can be "
"specified as single or multiple entries. Both IPv4 and/or IPv6 addresses are "
"supported"
msgstr ""
"<literal>${DNS_SERVER_V4}</literal> y/o <literal>${DNS_SERVER_V6}</literal>: "
"las direcciones IP de los servidores DNS que se van a usar, que pueden "
"especificarse como entradas únicas o múltiples. Se admiten direcciones IPv4 "
"y/o IPv6"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3786
msgid ""
"You can refer to <link xl:href=\"https://github.com/suse-edge/atip/tree/main/"
"telco-examples/edge-clusters\">SUSE Telco Cloud examples repo</link> for "
"more complex examples, including IPv6 only and dual-stack configurations."
msgstr ""
"En el <link xl:href=\"https://github.com/suse-edge/atip/tree/main/telco-"
"examples/edge-clusters\">repositorio de ejemplos de SUSE Telco Cloud</link> "
"encontrará ejemplos más complejos, incluidas configuraciones solo de IPv6 y "
"de doble pila."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3788
msgid ""
"Lastly, regardless of the network configuration details, ensure that the "
"secret is referenced by appending <literal>preprovisioningNetworkDataName</"
"literal> to the <literal>BaremetalHost</literal> object to successfully "
"enroll the host in the management cluster."
msgstr ""
"Por último, independientemente de los detalles de la configuración de red, "
"asegúrese de que se haga referencia al secreto añadiendo "
"<literal>preprovisioningNetworkDataName</literal> al objeto "
"<literal>BaremetalHost</literal> para inscribir correctamente el host en el "
"clúster de gestión."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3789
msgid ""
"If you need to deploy a multi-node cluster, the same process must be done "
"for each node."
msgstr ""
"Si necesita desplegar un clúster de varios nodos, debe realizar el mismo "
"proceso para cada nodo."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3790
msgid ""
"The <literal>Metal3DataTemplate</literal>, <literal>networkData</literal> "
"and <literal>Metal3 IPAM</literal> are currently not supported; only the "
"configuration via static secrets is fully supported."
msgstr ""
"Actualmente, <literal>Metal3DataTemplate</literal>, <literal>networkData</"
"literal> y <literal>Metal3 IPAM</literal> no se admiten; solo se admite "
"plenamente la configuración mediante secretos estáticos."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><title>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3792
msgid "Telco features (DPDK, SR-IOV, CPU isolation, huge pages, NUMA, etc.)"
msgstr ""
"Funciones para telecomunicaciones (DPDK, SR-IOV, aislamiento de CPU, páginas "
"enormes, NUMA, etc.)"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3793
msgid ""
"The directed network provisioning workflow allows to automate the Telco "
"features to be used in the downstream clusters to run Telco workloads on top "
"of those servers."
msgstr ""
"El flujo de trabajo de aprovisionamiento de red dirigida permite automatizar "
"las funciones de telecomunicaciones que se usarán en los clústeres "
"descendentes para ejecutar cargas de trabajo de telecomunicaciones en esos "
"servidores."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3795
msgid ""
"The image generated using <literal>EIB</literal>, as described in the "
"previous section (<xref linkend=\"eib-edge-image-connected\"/>), has to be "
"located in the management cluster exactly on the path you configured on this "
"section (<xref linkend=\"metal3-media-server\"/>)."
msgstr ""
"La imagen generada con <literal>EIB</literal>, que se describe en la sección "
"anterior (<xref linkend=\"eib-edge-image-connected\"/>), debe estar en el "
"clúster de gestión exactamente en la ruta que ha configurado en esa sección "
"(<xref linkend=\"metal3-media-server\"/>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3796
msgid ""
"The image generated using <literal>EIB</literal> has to include the specific "
"Telco packages following this section (<xref linkend=\"add-telco-feature-"
"eib\"/>)."
msgstr ""
"La imagen generada con <literal>EIB</literal> debe incluir los paquetes "
"específicos de telecomunicaciones que se indican en esa sección (<xref "
"linkend=\"add-telco-feature-eib\"/>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3799
msgid ""
"Use the following two sections as the base to enroll and provision the hosts:"
msgstr ""
"Use las dos secciones siguientes como base para inscribir y aprovisionar los "
"hosts:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3802
msgid "The Telco features covered in this section are the following:"
msgstr ""
"Las funciones de telecomunicaciones que se tratan en esta sección son las "
"siguientes:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3803
msgid "DPDK and VFs creation"
msgstr "DPDK y creación de funciones virtuales"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3804
msgid "SR-IOV and VFs allocation to be used by the workloads"
msgstr ""
"Asignación de SR-IOV y funciones virtuales que usarán las cargas de trabajo"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3805
msgid "CPU isolation and performance tuning"
msgstr "Aislamiento de CPU y optimización del rendimiento"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3806
msgid "Huge pages configuration"
msgstr "Configuración de páginas enormes"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3807
msgid "Kernel parameters tuning"
msgstr "Optimización de los parámetros del kernel"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><note><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3808
msgid ""
"For more information about the Telco features, see <xref linkend=\"atip-"
"features\"/>."
msgstr ""
"Para obtener más información sobre las funciones de telecomunicaciones, "
"consulte el <xref linkend=\"atip-features\"/>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3809
msgid ""
"The changes required to enable the Telco features shown above are all inside "
"the <literal>RKE2ControlPlane</literal> block in the provision file "
"<literal>capi-provisioning-example.yaml</literal>. The rest of the "
"information inside the file <literal>capi-provisioning-example.yaml</"
"literal> is the same as the information provided in the provisioning section "
"(<xref linkend=\"single-node-provision\"/>)."
msgstr ""
"Todos los cambios necesarios para habilitar las funciones de "
"telecomunicaciones indicados arriba se encuentran en el bloque "
"<literal>RKE2ControlPlane</literal> del archivo de aprovisionamiento "
"<literal>capi-provisioning-example.yaml</literal>. El resto de la "
"información contenida en el archivo <literal>capi-provisioning-example.yaml</"
"literal> es la misma que se proporciona en la sección sobre "
"aprovisionamiento (<xref linkend=\"single-node-provision\"/>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3810
msgid ""
"To make the process clear, the changes required on that block "
"(<literal>RKE2ControlPlane</literal>) to enable the Telco features are the "
"following:"
msgstr ""
"Para que el proceso quede claro, los cambios necesarios en ese bloque "
"(<literal>RKE2ControlPlane</literal>) para habilitar las funciones de "
"telecomunicaciones son los siguientes:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3811
msgid ""
"The <literal>preRKE2Commands</literal> to be used to execute the commands "
"before the <literal>RKE2</literal> installation process. In this case, use "
"the <literal>modprobe</literal> command to enable the <literal>vfio-pci</"
"literal> and the <literal>SR-IOV</literal> kernel modules."
msgstr ""
"Los comandos <literal>preRKE2Commands</literal> que se usarán para ejecutar "
"los comandos antes del proceso de instalación de <literal>RKE2</literal>. En "
"este caso, use el comando <literal>modprobe</literal> para habilitar los "
"módulos del kernel <literal>vfio-pci</literal> y <literal>SR-IOV</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3812
msgid ""
"The ignition file <literal>/var/lib/rancher/rke2/server/manifests/configmap-"
"sriov-custom-auto.yaml</literal> to be used to define the interfaces, "
"drivers and the number of <literal>VFs</literal> to be created and exposed "
"to the workloads."
msgstr ""
"El archivo de Ignition <literal>/var/lib/rancher/rke2/server/manifests/"
"configmap-sriov-custom-auto.yaml</literal> se usará para definir las "
"interfaces, los controladores y el número de <literal>funciones virtuales</"
"literal> que se crearán y expondrán a las cargas de trabajo."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3813
msgid ""
"The values inside the config map <literal>sriov-custom-auto-config</literal> "
"are the only values to be replaced with real values."
msgstr ""
"Los valores del mapa de configuración <literal>sriov-custom-auto-config</"
"literal> son los únicos que deben sustituirse por valores reales."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3814
msgid ""
"<literal>${RESOURCE_NAME1}</literal> — The resource name to be used for the "
"first <literal>PF</literal> interface (for example, <literal>sriov-resource-"
"du1</literal>). It is added to the prefix <literal>rancher.io</literal> to "
"be used as a label to be used by the workloads (for example, "
"<literal>rancher.io/sriov-resource-du1</literal>)."
msgstr ""
"<literal>${RESOURCE_NAME1}</literal>: el nombre del recurso que se va a usar "
"para la primera interfaz de función física <literal>PF</literal> (por "
"ejemplo, <literal>sriov-resource-du1</literal>). Se añade al prefijo "
"<literal>rancher.io</literal> para usarse como etiqueta que utilizarán las "
"cargas de trabajo (por ejemplo, <literal>rancher.io/sriov-resource-du1</"
"literal>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3815
msgid ""
"<literal>${SRIOV-NIC-NAME1}</literal> — The name of the first <literal>PF</"
"literal> interface to be used (for example, <literal>eth0</literal>)."
msgstr ""
"<literal>${SRIOV-NIC-NAME1}</literal>: el nombre de la primera interfaz de "
"función física <literal>PF</literal> que se usará (por ejemplo, "
"<literal>eth0</literal>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3816
msgid ""
"<literal>${PF_NAME1}</literal> — The name of the first physical function "
"<literal>PF</literal> to be used. Generate more complex filters using this "
"(for example, <literal>eth0#2-5</literal>)."
msgstr ""
"<literal>${PF_NAME1}</literal>: el nombre de la primera función física "
"<literal>PF</literal> que se usará. Con esto, puede generar filtros más "
"complejos (por ejemplo, <literal>eth0#2-5</literal>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3817
msgid ""
"<literal>${DRIVER_NAME1}</literal> — The driver name to be used for the "
"first <literal>VF</literal> interface (for example, <literal>vfio-pci</"
"literal>)."
msgstr ""
"<literal>${DRIVER_NAME1}</literal>: el nombre del controlador que se usará "
"para la primera interfaz de función virtual <literal>VF</literal> (por "
"ejemplo, <literal>vfio-pci</literal>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3818
msgid ""
"<literal>${NUM_VFS1}</literal> — The number of <literal>VFs</literal> to be "
"created for the first <literal>PF</literal> interface (for example, "
"<literal>8</literal>)."
msgstr ""
"<literal>${NUM_VFS1}</literal>: el número de <literal>funciones virtuales</"
"literal> que se crearán para la primera interfaz de función física "
"<literal>PF</literal> (por ejemplo, <literal>8</literal>)."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3819
msgid ""
"The <literal>/var/sriov-auto-filler.sh</literal> to be used as a translator "
"between the high-level config map <literal>sriov-custom-auto-config</"
"literal> and the <literal>sriovnetworknodepolicy</literal> which contains "
"the low-level hardware information. This script has been created to abstract "
"the user from the complexity to know in advance the hardware information. No "
"changes are required in this file, but it should be present if we need to "
"enable <literal>sr-iov</literal> and create <literal>VFs</literal>."
msgstr ""
"El archivo <literal>/var/sriov-auto-filler.sh</literal> que se usará como "
"traductor entre el mapa de configuración general <literal>sriov-custom-auto-"
"config</literal> y el archivo <literal>sriovnetworknodepolicy</literal>, que "
"contiene la información de hardware de bajo nivel. Este guion se ha creado "
"para evitar al usuario la complejidad que supone que tenga que conocer de "
"antemano la información de hardware. No es necesario realizar cambios en "
"este archivo, pero debe estar presente si necesitamos habilitar <literal>sr-"
"iov</literal> y crear <literal>funciones virtuales</literal>."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><itemizedlist><listitem><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3820
msgid "The kernel arguments to be used to enable the following features:"
msgstr ""
"Los argumentos del kernel que se usarán para habilitar las siguientes "
"funciones:"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><informaltable><tgroup><tbody><row><entry><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3821
msgid "Parameter"
msgstr "Parámetro"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><informaltable><tgroup><tbody><row><entry><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3822
msgid "Value"
msgstr "Valor"

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><informaltable><tgroup><tbody><row><entry><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3826
msgid "Isolate the cores 1-30 and 33-62."
msgstr "Aísla los núcleos 1-30 y 33-62."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><informaltable><tgroup><tbody><row><entry><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3829
msgid ""
"Allows the kernel to skew the timer interrupts across the isolated CPUs."
msgstr ""
"Permite al kernel distribuir las interrupciones del temporizador entre las "
"CPU aisladas."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><informaltable><tgroup><tbody><row><entry><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3832
msgid ""
"Allows the kernel to run the timer tick on a single CPU when the system is "
"idle."
msgstr ""
"Permite al kernel ejecutar la marca del temporizador en una sola CPU cuando "
"el sistema está inactivo."

#. type: Content of: <book><part><chapter><section><informaltable><tgroup><tbody><row><entry><para>
#: l10n/source/edge.xml:3835
msgid ""
"kernel boot parameter is the current main interface to configure full "
"dynticks along with CPU Isolation."
msgstr ""
"El parámetro de arranque del kernel es la interfaz principal actual para "
